<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Basil Guacamole</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Dip</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing-div>
        <title/>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Lemon/lime</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>dash</unit></amt>
          <item>Olive oil (optional)</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Avacados</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty/>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Chiles to taste (I found 2 Jalapenos a bit mild)</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>large</unit></amt>
          <item>Ripe tomato</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty/>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Garlic/salt etc.</item></ing></ing-div>
      <ing-div>
        <title>THE SHOCK INGREDIENTS</title>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Sq. inches green pepper</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>large</unit></amt>
          <item>Fresh basil leaves</item></ing></ing-div></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  I thought I'd share with you this variant on the traditional Guacamole I
  knocked up last night:
  
  I didn't expect to taste the basil but it really shone through very
  strongly.  I put this down to its strong affinity to tomato.
  
  Also I was concerned the pepper would spoil the other flavour but its aroma
  blended in to produced a slightly sweeter aftertaste.
  
  CHILE-HEADS ARCHIVES
  
  From the Chile-Heads recipe list.  Downloaded from Glen's MM Recipe
  Archive, http://www.erols.com/hosey.
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
